Class WindowsNewUserAccessAction

java.lang.Object
  au.edu.uts.eng.remotelabs.rigclient.action.access.WindowsNewUserAccessAction
All Implemented Interfaces:
IAccessAction, IAction
Deprecated. 

@Deprecated
public class WindowsNewUserAccessAction
extends java.lang.Object
implements IAccessAction

Action which creates a new user on Windows. This action does assign access to be able login remotely using the RemoteDesktopAccessAction class to add the newly created user to the "Remote Desktop Users" group.
The name of the new user is the name of the assigned user if it does not already exist, otherwise it is the name of the user with a incremented number appended to it as needed to make the name unique. The password is randomly generated with alphanumeric characters and of length 8.
The WindowsNewUserController primitive controller class is set with the newly created user login credentials and these may accessed with the getCredentialsAction action method.
